Description: Blue Blood Brewing Company was founded on the premise of a great friendship and love of great beer.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Blue Blood Brewing Company was founded on the premise of a great friendship and love of great beer. Its founders work hard, and that hard work is translated into the beer that they brew. Although the road to the Brewery opening had some detours, this Lincoln, Nebraska Brewery has proudly been producing beers since December 2011. Brian Podwinski, Blue Blood Brewing Company President and Co-Founder, began his first career as a Police Officer with the Lincoln Police Department in 2000. Unfortunately his policing career was cut short due to an injury which forced him to retire from the department in 2006. His sidelined career created extra time and the search for a new passion, so Brian began brewing beer at home. Immediately after brewing his first batch from a kit, he was hooked. Brian researched and studied the art of brewing beer and experimented with different ales, ingredients, and formulas. Taking notice of Brianâs spectacular beers, Jason Goodwin began brewing with him. The thought of opening a brewery seemed like an unobtainable goal, but it seemed to become more reachable the more the two brewed (and in turn drank). Another year of research and planning ultimately reaped the ultimate reward. Blue Blood Brewing Company came to fruition after hours of preparing prefect recipes, finding a wonderful location, and setting up well-researched equipment.
